'''[[drinking]]-[[horn]]'''
# A drinking-vessel made from the horn of an animal.
#:*'''1997''': He put down his sword and helmet and took the drinking-horn that was served to him, and finished it. — ‘Egil's Saga’, tr. Bernard Scudder, ''The Sagas of Icelanders'' (Penguin 2001, p. 91)

